fields.label_text:
CLOSET OR CABINET OF MIRRORS
ITALIAN (Lombardy); about 1780

Carved and gilded pine.  The parquetry floor of walnut and ash.  The top course of coffering in the ceiling is lacking.

Candelabra would have been placed on the small console tables where the modern lamps now stand and, like these, would have been reflected in the mirrors behind.

Given by Sir Alfred Chester Beatty, FSA, LL.D. Dsc.
